{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πραγμᾰτ-ικός</b>, ή, όν, <br /> <b>fit for action</b> or <b>business, businesslike, statesmanlike,</b> later Greek for πρακτικός, βασιλεύς, ἄνδρες, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 7.11.2, 7.12.2, +others\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; <b>pragmatici homines,</b> men <b>of the world,</b> men <b>of affairs,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Cicero, M. Tullius Orator et Philosophus “Epistulae ad Atticum” 2.20.1 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; <b>wise and prudent men,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"Vett. Val. 17.22 \">Refs</a>]; πραγματική, ={ἐπιστήμη τῶν ἀνθρωπίνων πραγμάτων}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Andronicus Epigrammaticus Rhod. p.574 \">Refs</a>] M. <i>adverb</i> <b>-κῶς</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Cicero, M. Tullius Orator et Philosophus “Epistulae ad Quintum Fratrem” 2.14.2. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <i>substantive</i> πραγματικός, ὁ, <b>agent, attorney,</b> π. τῆς πόλεως, τοῦ νομοῦ, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Inscription Magn.” 189 (2nd c.AD), “PAmh.” 2.107.15 (2nd c.AD),compare “SIG” 888.101 (Scaptopara, 3rd c.AD). \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__2.b</b></Level4> Latin <i>pragmaticus, legal adviser,</i> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Cicero, M. Tullius Orator et Philosophus “de Or.” 1.45.59, 1st c.AD: Quintilianus Rhetor Latinus “Inst.” 12.3.4, 1st c.AD: Juvenalis, D. Junius Poeta Latinus 7.123. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__2.c</b></Level4> <b>civil official,</b> opposed to military officer, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PTeb.” 58.18 (2nd c.BC), “OGI” 139.7 (Egypt, 2nd c.BC), 669.21, +others ([prev. passage] 1st c.AD)\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; <b>civilian,</b> opposed to στρατιωτικός, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 14.1.13; ἱερόδουλοι καὶ π. τοῦ ἱεροῦ LXX.1Esd.8.22. \">LXX+2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> π. τύπος, νόμος, = Latin <i>pragmatica sanctio,</i> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.AD: Justinianus Imperator “Novellae” 7.2.1, “Codex Justinianus [4th-6th c.AD]” 1.3.38.6. \">Refs 6th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> of things, <br /><Level3><b>__II.1</b></Level3> of history, <b>political</b> (including <b>military</b>), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 1.2.8, 9.2.4, +others, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Galba” 2, etc.\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; π. ἀποφάσεις <b>political</b> utterances, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 32.2.7. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> of speech or action, <b>able, prudent, statesmanlike,</b> ἔργον, λόγοι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 3.116.7, 36.5.1; τρόπος [prev. author] 23.5.5 \">Refs</a>]; ὥστε μὴ ὑποπτεῦσαί τι περὶ αὐτοῦ πραγματικόν anything <b>machiavellian,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 30.27.2, compare 30.19.11 \">Refs</a>]. <i>adverb</i> <b>-κῶς</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 2.13.1, +others\">Refs</a>]; <b>by statecraft,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 31.10.6. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>relating to subject-matter,</b> opposed to style, ὁ π. τόπος, opposed to ὁ λεκτικός, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis “de Compositione Verborum” 1 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]: <i>superlative</i>, -ωτάτη εὕρεσις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Hermogenes Rhetor “περὶ εὑρέσεως” 1.1. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> <b>relating to fact,</b> θεωρήματα, ζήτησις, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “De rerum natura - Wien. Stud.” 28 “fragment” 4 (p.5 V.), 2nd c.BC: Demetrius Lacon Philosophus “Herc.” 1014.62; πίστις 5th c.AD: Syrianus Philosophus et Rhetor “in Hermog.” i p.57 R. (variant): -κή, ἡ, \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] <b>deliberation on matter of fact</b> or <b>on action,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work]ii p.161 R.; π.ἔγγραφος, ἄγραφος, [prev. work] p.162 R. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__III.2.b</b></Level4> <b>material</b> (opposed to formal, verbal), διαφωνία [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.AD: Simplicius Philosophus “in Aristotelis de Caelo commentaria - Comm. in Arist. Graeca” 640.28 \">Refs 6th c.AD+</a>]. <i>adverb</i> -κῶς, ζητεῖν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Rh.” 2.238 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus, compare 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.960b; διαφέρεσθαι [prev. work]1113c; τὸ π. ἀπορούμενον\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] difficulty <b>arising from facts</b> (opposed to verbal), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.AD: Simplicius Philosophus “in Aristotelis Physica commentaria - Comm. in Arist. Graeca” 1289.35 \">Refs 6th c.AD+</a>]: <i>superlative</i>, ἐν τοῖς Στωικοῖς - ώτατα φιλοσοφῆσαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Porphyrius Tyrius Philosophus “de Abstinentia - Porphyrii Opuscula” 4.8: opposed to ψυχικῶς, στοιχειακῶς, Anon.in Westermann “Mythogr.” p.328. \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> πραγματικόν, τό, in Magic, <b>effective spell,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" PMag.Par. 1.2432. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__V</b></Level2> <b>troublesome, formidable,</b> of a citadel, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 4.70.10; λίαν δυσάλωτος καὶ π. πόλις 4th-3rd c.BC: Berosus Historicus cited in 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus “contra Apionem” 1.20 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; of an attack, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 5.5.4; ἀήττητα καὶ π. πλήθη [prev. author] 1.35.5. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G20994","accentedUnicode":"πραγματι